Kano State governor, Dr. Abdullahi Umar Ganduje has confirmed the first COVID-19 case in the state. A top government official had earlier confided to LEADERSHIP that the patient is a retired technocrat, who returned from Lagos recently and had shown symptoms of COVID 19
Governor Abdullahi Umar Ganduje after a crucial meeting with health officials, informed the public officially of the sad development. The patient was diagnosed at the reactivated COVID-19 laboratory test centre at the Amimu Kano Teaching Hospital where he tested positive.
He is said to have moved to the isolation centre at Kwanar Dawaki, Kano
It was gathered that investigation is on for contact tracing.